Deportation Agency Ignored 1.6 Million Visa Overstays Under Obama   AP 
By Stephen Dinan - The Washington Times 
The government flagged more than 1.6 million foreign visitors for overstaying their visas from 2013 to 2015, but deportation agents said they fell too low on President Obamaâ€™s list of priorities to bother targeting for removal, according to a watchdog report released Monday.
